'''Dick van Burik''' (born 29 November 1973) is a retired [[Netherlands|Dutch]] professional [[Association football|footballer]] who played as a [[Defender (football)|central defender]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.kicker.de/news/fussball/bundesliga/vereine/1-bundesliga/2006-07/hertha-bsc-29/1685/spieler_dick-van-burik.html | title = van Burik, Dick | language = German | publisher = kicker.de | accessdate = 12 February 2011}}</ref>
==Club career== Born in [[Utrecht (city)|Utrecht]], Van Burik played in the [[Eredivisie]] with [[AFC Ajax|Ajax]], [[NAC Breda|NAC]] and [[FC Utrecht]].<ref>[http://www.nac.nl/108/newsid/7941/Van-Burik-naar-FC-Utrecht.html Van Burik naar FC Utrecht] - NAC {{nl|icon}}</ref>
However, he would be best known for a 10-year stint with German [[Bundesliga]] outfit [[Hertha BSC]], where he would be a defensive mainstay for a side that participated in five [[UEFA Cup]] editions and the [[1999–2000 UEFA Champions League]] (as a result of a third league place in [[1998–99 Bundesliga|1998–99]], with Van Burik subsequently appearing in ten Champions League contests, as Hertha reached the second group stage).
Van Burik was dismissed by Hertha after the club accused him of playing a role in the departure of teammate [[Jérôme Boateng]], who was a client of van Burik's father and football agent Karel.<ref>[https://www.trouw.nl/home/wegen-van-burik-en-hertha-bsc-scheiden~a00cb2ff/ Wegen Van Burik en Hertha BSC scheiden] - Trouw {{nl|icon}}</ref> He subsequently retired in June 2007.
==Retirement== He was assistant manager at [[SC Heerenveen]] from February to June 2010.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.worldfootball.net/spieler_profil/dick-van-burik/ | title = Dick van Burik | publisher = worldfootball.net | accessdate = 12 February 2011}}</ref> He runs a football agency with his father and a coating company, VB Coatings.<ref>[http://www.quotenet.nl/Nieuws/Dick-van-Burik-over-zijn-eerste-miljoen-Ik-onderneem-zoals-ik-voetbalde-159085 Dick van Burik over zijn eerste miljoen: 'Ik onderneem zoals ik voetbalde'] - Quotenet {{nl|icon}}</ref>
