'''Fikirte Addis''' (born 1981) is an Ethiopian [[fashion designer]].<ref>{{citation|author=Catherine Chambers|title=African Culture|date=1 July 2012|publisher=Heinemann Library|isbn=978-1-4329-6776-5|page=27}}</ref> In 2009, Addis formed her own label–Yefiker Design–which creates clothes that are modern interpretations of traditional Ethiopian dress.<ref>{{citation|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/business-26627406 |title=Ethiopia's clothes firms aim to fashion global sales |work=[[BBC NEWS]] |date=March 19, 2014 |author=James Jeffrey }}</ref> Her work rose to prominence by 2011, when she was a featured designer in the second annual [[Africa Fashion Week New York|Africa Fashion Week]] in New York City.<ref>{{citation |url=http://www.wnyc.org/story/144887-african-fashion-week/ |title=Africa Fashion Week Kicks off on Monday |author=Luna Lin |date=July 10, 2011 |work=[[WNYC]] }}</ref>

