[[File:Rektor Jan Grund.jpg|thumb|Jan Grund]]
'''Jan Grund''' (born 22 July 1946) is a Norwegian academic.

He graduated with the [[cand.oecon.]] degree in 1972.<ref name=hiak>{{cite web|url=http://www.hiak.no/index.php?ID=29&lang=nor&displayitem=193&module=news |title=Sterke fagmiljøer, økt samarbeid og god ledelse |last=Eriksen |first=Jan |date=31 March 2008 |publisher=Akershus University College |language=Norwegian |accessdate=22 April 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090418172937/http://www.hiak.no/index.php?ID=29 |archivedate=18 April 2009 |df= }}</ref> He was hired as [[Rector (academia)|rector]] of [[Akershus University College]] in December 2007, and assumed office in April 2008.<ref>{{cite news|title=Første rektor ved Høgskolen i Akershus|date=19 December 2007|agency=Norwegian News Agency|language=Norwegian}}</ref> He was formerly a professor of health administration at the [[Norwegian School of Management]]'s Department of Public Governance. He has also been [[chair (official)|chair]] of [[Oslo Nye Teater]] and a member of the board of [[Oslo Kino]] and [[Black Box Teater]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Jan Grund (61)|date=28 October 2008|work=Romerikes Blad|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

He is a son of [[Inger Louise Valle]]. He is married, and lives in [[Ullern]].<ref name=hiak/>

